<div type="definition">
<p>HUMAN SUMMONED in LAW COURT TO EXPLAIN what s/he KNOWS that is IMPORTANT to LITIGATION.</p>
    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2023-09-12T17:12:33.186+09:00">
            <p>HUMAN WHO is BELIEVED TO KNOW IMPORTANT THINGS THAT are NEEDED in LITIGATION OR DISCUSSION.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for bearing witness to something or against something is zhèng 證.</p>
<p>2. Zuǒ 左 is occasionally used to refer to a witness for or against something.</p>
        </div>
